sequenceDiagram
    title Google Voice — Incoming Call Flow
    participant Browser
    participant GV_WSS as voice.telephony.goog (SIP WebSocket)
    participant OGHP as OGHP Gateway (74.125.39.x)

    Note over Browser,GV_WSS: Incoming INVITE (server-initiated)
    GV_WSS->>Browser: INVITE sip:v5ad2hhq@local (SDP offer from Google)
    Browser-->>GV_WSS: 100 Trying
    Browser-->>GV_WSS: 180 Ringing

    Note over Browser,OGHP: WebRTC Setup
    Browser->>Browser: setRemoteDescription(offer)
    Browser->>Browser: createAnswer → setLocalDescription(answer)
    Browser->>OGHP: ICE candidates (host + SRFLX)

    Note over Browser,GV_WSS: Call Answered
    Browser-->>GV_WSS: 183 Session Progress (SDP answer)
    Browser-->>GV_WSS: 200 OK
    GV_WSS->>Browser: ACK

    Note over Browser,OGHP: Codec Renegotiation (3 rounds)
    Browser->>GV_WSS: re-INVITE (updated SDP)
    GV_WSS-->>Browser: 200 OK (updated SDP answer)
    Browser->>GV_WSS: ACK

    Note over Browser,OGHP: Bidirectional Audio
    Browser->>OGHP: RTP/SRTP (Opus)
    OGHP-->>Browser: RTP/SRTP (Opus)

    Note over Browser,GV_WSS: Call Terminated
    Browser->>GV_WSS: BYE
    GV_WSS-->>Browser: 200 OK

    %% Confidence: High — 19 RTC events + SIP frames from live incoming call
